==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hysterical
<hw>Hys*ter"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>hystericus</ets>, Gr.
<?/, fr. <grk>"yste`ra</grk> the womb; perh. akin to <?/ latter, later,
and E. <ets>utter</ets>, <ets>out</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to hysteria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With no <qex>hysteric</qex> weakness or feverish excitement, they
preserved their peace and patience.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In a state of hysteria; affected, or troubled, with
hysterics; uncontrollably emotional; convulsive, fitful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In a state of panic or behaving in a wild irrational
manner, due to fear or emotional trauma.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Resembling hysteria; <as>as, <ex>hysterical</ex>
laughter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hysterical</ent>⟦br⟧

